<h1 id="accrue-time-off-based-on-hours-worked">Accrue time off based on hours worked</h1>

<h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
<p>Organizations with hourly employees can award time off based on hours worked instead of tenure with the organization. The hours worked data is typically stored in a time and attendance system.</p>
<h2 id="leave-plans">Leave plans</h2>
<p>Within the leave plan, the accrual type can either be months of service or hours worked. When hours worked is selected, there are two types of hours to use for the accural: regular and overtime.</p>
<p>To set up a leave plan to use hours worked, follow these steps:</p>
<ol>
<li>On the <strong>Leave and absence plans</strong> page, click <strong>Create new plan</strong>.</li>
<li>Enter a name for your leave plan.</li>
<li>Select the accrual frequency for the plan.</li>
<li>Select the start date for the plan.</li>
<li>Choose the accrual period basis and select the employee-specific date, if applicable.</li>
<li>For the accrual schedule, select <strong>Hours worked</strong> for the accrual type.</li>
<li>Select the type of hours to be used for the accrual.</li>
<li>Enter the number of hours worked and the associated accrual amount, minimum balance, and maximum carryforward or grant amount.</li>
</ol>
<p>Accrual processing for hours worked plans uses the accrual frequency, along with the accrual period basis, to determine the hours to be accrued.</p>
